h4 Toast
p.-text
  | Toasts are unobtrusive alerts used to display brief, auto-expiring information.
  | To use a toast alert, apply the class <code>-toast</code> and ensure the alert
  | is placed in the top right corner or bottom left corner of the screen.

.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    each val, type in {success:'icon-circle-check', danger:'icon-circle-warning', warning:'icon-warning', info:'icon-circle-info', muted:'icon-circle-info'}
      .m-alert.-toast.-titled.-m--2(class=`-${type}`)
        .m-alert__content
          i.a-icon(class =`${val} -text--${type}`)
          div
            div(class=`a-h5`)= type
            = `This is a ${type} alert`
        button(class='a-btn -icon -close -sm')
          .a-btn__content
            i.a-icon.icon-x
